<item>
            <title>[LU-4681] llmount.sh error message when parsing NID can be better defined</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-4681</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;When running llmount.sh it can error when trying to parse the NID while formatting the OSTs.  It errors with the following:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Formatting mgs, mds, osts&lt;br/&gt;
Format mds1: /tmp/lustre-mdt1&lt;br/&gt;
Format ost1: /tmp/lustre-ost1&lt;br/&gt;
mkfs.lustre: Can&apos;t parse NID &apos;lustremaster@tcp&apos;&lt;br/&gt;
mkfs.lustre: exiting with 1 (Operation not permitted)&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This error could be better stated by saying that &apos;hostname&apos; with address needs to be added to /etc/hosts, or something to give users a better idea how to fix this problem.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
